++ **Background of the Incident - The Chaos Insurgency's Intentions**
[[include :scp-wiki:component:image-block name=https://scp-sandbox-3.wdfiles.com/local--files/collab%3Anicotranslate2/nico-table-one.png|caption=Relationship diagram of each organization Click to enlarge|width=240px|link="*https://scp-sandbox-3.wdfiles.com/local--files/collab%3Anicotranslate2/nico-table-one.png"|align=right]]

　Global order following [http://scp-int.wikidot.com/scp-1710-jp 12/07] has been constructed mainly by four organizations: the Foundation, the Global Occult Coalition (GOC), Prometheus Laboratories and the United States of America. The new paranormal organizational system of these four powers, which exert influence in various fields such as politics, the military, science and the economy, is referred to as the Gulf of Mexico Agreement, after the common name of [[[operation-cannery-row-document-2013-451a3|SUSEOCT]]] (Southern United States Extranormal Organization Cooperation Treaty), which served as a jumping off point. For our Japanese readers, SUSEOCT is the American equivalent of [http://scp-int.wikidot.com/jagpato-hub JAGPATO] (Japanese Anomalous Groups Peace and Amity Treaty Organization).

　However, the collusion between the four major powers, which had been observed even before the 12/07 Incident, has become increasingly corrupt since the establishment of the Gulf regime. A prime example being the Tamarack Building scandal, which we have recently reported on, in which the Foundation and the FBI Unusual Incidents Unit (UIU) regularly exchange [[[scp-2635|some sort of paranormal asset]]]. Although spokespersons for the Foundation and the UIU have claimed that this is "just a containment measure," it is clearly a cover for bribes or money laundering, and our interviews with Site-58 have always been denied due to the Foundation's cover-up efforts.

　Under these circumstances, the 9/11 incident was carried out by the Chaos Insurgency (CI), a military paranormal organization that broke away from the Foundation. The CI has been excessively opposed to the Foundation from the time of its inception, and this hostility to the Gulf regime is believed to be the reason for this incident.
